{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"df65f0ae-e902-43d7-8485-bf652244672f","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` **natively supports MTP**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 opt-in bridge and is **no longer needed**. Since you already have `EnableMSTestRunner`, you just need to remove that property.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_018d7jTKXdKCDvukV6J2bbqT","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01PNvVxuQ8gzsUyvFvanvrcF","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8996f3cfb6434731a25d47b2a865e949/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8996f3cfb6434731a25d47b2a865e949/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"6c002a39-725a-46dc-a8d2-b7662b86c58c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true. They want to know about native MTP support in .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Starting with .NET 10 SDK, when you have `EnableMSTestRunner` (or equivalent for other frameworks), `dotnet test` will automatically use MTP. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt into the MTP integration, but in .NET 10 it's the default behavior.\n\n\nSo I can simplify their project file by removing that property entirely since MTP is now the default when `EnableMSTestRunner` is enabled.","outputTokens":646},"id":"de0e8773-f995-4e09-a5fe-7f7ec2ea5c40","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:55:49.827Z","parentId":"a51535a3-bc08-4ded-bdc2-c5412db99bbd"}
