{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d6003298-0d3e-440d-9704-cba84553ded9","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` → remove it.** In .NET 10, `dotnet test` was rewritten to use MTP natively. This property was only needed in .NET 9 to opt into the preview MTP integration.\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner` → keep it.** This tells MSTest to produce an MTP-based executable, which `dotnet test` in .NET 10 discovers and runs automatically.\n- **`OutputType Exe` → keep it.** Required for MTP-based test projects.\n\nYour updated `.csproj` is now:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual — it will use MTP under the hood with no extra configuration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6c002a39-725a-46dc-a8d2-b7662b86c58c","outputTokens":288},"id":"b8e571a0-78db-4fa5-9300-99f90d459fcc","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:55:58.264Z","parentId":"d7c1b2c2-bbc3-4c33-955b-80dea106be93"}
